text.tspan: The artificial intelligence of Forestly is a computer
system that tries to learn patterns from a large
amount of data by means of machine learning.
Therefore, a database of many mushroom images is
necessary for the identification of mushroom species.
With this database, a digital model is created that can
be used to classify new images. The model is built up
in different layers. The first layer, for example,
recognizes rather abstract features such as lines or
simple shapes in images. Later layers then recognize
increasingly complex patterns that are composed of
the simpler lines and shapesâ€”for example, whether
the cap is spherical or funnel-shaped, or whether the
mushroom has lamellae or tubes underneath the cap.

When a new image is entered, the AI outputs a
certain result based on the model, and indicates
how confident it is with its prediction.
